<HEAD>Pope Expresses Grief Over Armenian Earthquake</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VATICAN CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pope John Paul II expressed his grief today
over the killer earthquake in Armenia.
   ``In this hour of trial, I am closer than ever to the Armenian
people, who are always present in my prayers and my pastoral
concerns,'' John Paul said in remarks from his apartment window on
the Roman Catholic Feast of the Immaculate Conception.
   He told several thousand people gathered in St. Peter's Square
