<HEAD>No Contract Renewal For Jessica Hahn</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHOENIX (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Jessica Hahn, whose sexual encounter with TV
evangelist Jim Bakker led to his downfall, won't get another
contract at radio station KOY, the station's general manager says.
   Ms. Hahn, 29, began work in September under a 30-day contract,
initially with the morning crew at the top 40 station. That contract
was renewed and extended to year's end, and she was moved to the
station's evening show.
   This week, KOY General Manager Mike Horne said Ms. Hahn's
services won't be required when her agreement with the station ends
Dec. 31. He did not say why her contract wasn't renewed.
