<HEAD>Recent Military Air Crashes in West Germany
^With AM-Germany-Air Crashes Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FRANKFURT, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a list of recent military
air crashes in West Germany.
   March 31, 1988, a U.S. Air Force F-16 jet crashes in the West
German town of Forst, killing the pilot and a man on the ground.
   April 5, the two-man crew aboard a U.S. Army helicopter is killed
when the aircraft crashes near Stuttgart.
   May 6, a British Royal Air Force Chinook helicopter strikes a
loading ramp with its rotor blade at Hanover airport at an air show,
killing two crewmen.
   May 20, a British Royal Air Force pilot is killed when his
Harrier jet crashs near Gutersloh.
   June 9, a U.S. Army UH1H helicopter crashes near Krumbach in
Bavaria, killing the three-man crew.
   June 14, the co-pilot of a OH58 U.S. Army helicopter is killed
when it crashes in Starnberg lake near Munich.
   June 15, the two-man West German crew of a Phantom jet fighter is
killed when it crashes near the town of Coesfeld.
   June 29, a U.S. Air Force pilot is killed when two F-16s collide
while flying near Mainz.
   July 3, nine people aboard a West German military helicopter are
killed when it crashes in the Bavarian Alps.
   July 26, the pilot of an ultra-light private plane dies in a
collision with a West German air force Tornado jet flying near
Munich.
   Aug. 28, 70 people die after three Italian Air Force stunt jets
collide at an air show at the U.S. Ramstein Air Base and one of the
planes plows into spectators at the event.
   Sept. 7, British Royal Air Force pilot is killed in a crash of a
Jaguar military jet near the town of Calw in the West Germany's
Black Forest region.
</TEXT>
