<HEAD>Skier Killed by Avalanche</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ZURICH, Switzerland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An avalanche roared down Mount Titlis
in the Swiss Alps on Thursday, killing a skier at about the
7,500-foot level, rescuers said.
   Search teams using dogs needed 50 minutes to locate the woman,
who was found alive but critically injured. She died shortly after a
helicopter brought her to Lucerne main hospital, the Swiss Air
Rescue Service said.
   A two-hour search turned up no other victims.
   Avalanches killed 25 people in Switzerland last year, slightly
below the average of the last 50 years.
