<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Italy-Arms,0139</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Two Suitcases of Arms Seized on Train</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COMO, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Border police seized two suitcases of
submachine guns and other arms on a Hamburg-Milan train, authorities
said Thursday.
   The luggage was not claimed by anyone, said Lt. Raffaele Ditroia
of the Finance Police, which guards the border.
   The suitcases contained two submachine guns, two semiautomatic
rifles and more than 100 boxes of ammunition, police said.
   Witnesses said a man got on the train at the border town of
Chiasso, Switzerland, on Tuesday night, put the suitcases in the
luggage rack in a second-class compartment and got off, police said.
   Italian border police doing routine luggage checks discovered the
arms.
   No one tried to claim the bags when the train from arrived in
Milan and no arrests were made, Ditroia said.
</TEXT>
