<DATELINE>BURLINGTON, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two boys have won spots on the
cheerleading squad at a middle school, resolving a sex
discrimination dispute that arose after school officials said
tryouts were for girls only.
   Three boys tried out last week for the Har-Bur Middle School team
that will cheer at basketball games, but administrators told them
the school had not planned for a coeducational squad.
