<HEAD>Auto Production Hits 1 Million Mark</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   South Korea's production of motor
vehicles since the start of this year reached 1,000,660 as of
Thursday, hitting 1 million annually for the first time, automakers
reported.
   The tally is expected to reach 1.09 million vehicles by the
year's end, compared with the previous annual record of 979,739
vehicles in 1987, they said.
   A series of labor protests early this year reduced car production
by 200,000, but Korean automakers increased output in the latter
half to exceed the milestone, the industry officials said.
   The officials listed Hyundai Motor Co.'s production so far this
year at 594,645 vehicles, followed by Kia Motors Corp. with 225,267
and Daewoo Motor Co. with 150,047 vehicles. There are a few other
small automakers in South Korea.
