<DATELINE>NORTHBROOK, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two flashy domestic models top Allstate
Insurance Co.'s annual list of automobile insurance rates, but the
insurer says other U.S.-made models dominate the lower end of the
rate scale.
   The Chevrolet Camaro IROC-Z28 and the Pontiac Firebird TransAm _
both made by General Motors Corp. _ are being charged 100 percent to
140 percent higher than standard rate levels for collision and
comprehensive coverages, according to the survey released Wednesday
of 1987 and 1988 models of foreign and domestic cars.
   Forty-three of the 49 cars being charged 10 percent to 40 percent
less than standard rates were domestic models, the report said.
