<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Americans took out $3.56 billion more in
consumer debt than they paid off in October, reflecting a rebound in
consumer spending, the government says.
   The Federal Reserve said Wednesday the October increase followed
a tiny $2 million rise in debt during September, the smallest change
in six years. Consumer credit fell by $81 million in October 1982 at
the bottom of the last recession.
</TEXT>
