this year than in 1987 as consumer confidence runs high and more
people are working, according to a new survey.
   The Conference Board, in its annual Christmas spending survey,
said Wednesday that spending for holiday gifts would total $37
billion this year, up from $35 billion in 1987. The survey found
that the typical family would spend about $325 on gifts.
