regulators to close or rescue failed institutions.
   The Federal Home Loan Bank Board said capital _ representing the
difference between loans and other assets and savers' deposits and
other liabilities _ edged up by $507 million in October following
advances of $2.47 billion September and $6.11 bilion in August.
