deficit reduction comes from spending cuts or tax increases.
   The high-level advisory panel received a study Wednesday prepared
by the Congressional Budget Office which showed that a full-scale
assault on the budget deficit will not cause a recession as long as
the Federal Reserve helps out by lowering interest rates to offset
the reduced federal spending.
