<HEAD>High Court Blocks Joint GEC-Siemens Bid For Plessey</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The High Court on Thursday temporarily blocked
General Electric Co. PLC and Siemens AG from proceeding with their
joint 1.7 billion-pound, or $3.1 billion, bid for the British
electronics company Plessey Co. PLC.
   The court granted the injunction on the grounds that the
GEC-Siemens bid violates the competition rules in the Treaty of
Rome, the founding charter of the European Community, Plessey said.
   The court injunction will remain in force until Monday, when a
full hearing will take place in the High Court.
   GEC, which has no ties with the similarly named American company,
had no immediate comment, said spokesman Peter Gillibrand. Neither
did Siemens, spokesman Rod Tucker said.
