<2ND_LINE>BC-Auto Prodn,0156</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Only version planned.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
260,735 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's
260,840, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago,
in which 228,874 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 166,892 cars this week,
compared with 163,995 a week ago and 149,958 in the same week in
1987.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 93,846,
compared with last week's 96,845 and last year's 78,916.
   Canadian automakers were to build 17,527 cars this week, down
from 18,347 a week ago and from last year's 21,720.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 21,684, compared
with 21,147 a week ago and 19,380 in the same week last year.
</TEXT>
