<1ST_LINE>r f AM-Citizens-Merger     12-08 0163</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Citizens-Merger,0171</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Last Obstacle to Citizens-Scotland Bank Merger Cleared</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The $440 million acquisition of Citizens
Financial Group by the Royal Bank of Scotland cleared its final
obstacle Thursday when a Massachusetts regulatory agency approved
the merger.
   The deal needed clearance by the Massachusetts Board of Bank
Incorporation because Providence-based Citizens recently acquired a
Massachusetts bank, Fairhaven Savings Bank.
   The merger with the Royal Bank of Scotland already had been
approved by shareholders and the Federal Reserve Board.
   Citizens, which has $2.9 billion in assets, will become the
American flagship of the Scottish bank. The combined companies will
operate in several countries with assets of $38.7 billion.
   Citizens President George Graboys has said the merger will help
Citizens compete in the crowded New England banking business. Two
other major Rhode Island banks, Fleet National Bank and Hospital
Trust National Bank, also have merged with out-of-state banks in
recent years.
   Citizens said the merger would be completed later this month.
</TEXT>
