barrels daily in the previous week and 13,170,000 barrels daily a
year ago.
   Crude runs east of California averaged 10,827,000 barrels daily
compared with 10,297,000 the previous week and 10,791,000 a year ago.
   Motor gasoline production for the latest week amounted to
7,385,000 barrels a day, compared with 6,984,000 barrels a day in
the previous week and 7,072,000 a day a year ago.
   East of California motor gasoline production was 6,096,000 a day
compared with 5,779,000 a day last week and 5,848,000 a day a year
ago.
   Motor gasoline stocks at the end of the latest week were
219,535,000 barrels, versus 216,648,000 a week earlier and
225,310,000 a year ago.
   East of California motor gasoline stocks totaled 189,691,000
barrels compared with 187,411,000 in the previous week and
196,913,000 barrels last year.
   Daily average gross crude oil and lease condensate production for
the week ended Friday was 8,032,000 barrels compared with 8,397,000
last year.
   Crude oil stocks totaled 337,703,000 barrels at the close of last
week, against 340,371,000 a week previous and 352,289,000 a year ago.
   East of California crude stocks amounted to 254,908,000 barrels,
compared with 259,178,000 a week earlier.
   Daily imports east of California for the week ended Friday were
crude oil, 5,028,000 barrels, residual fuel oil, 647,000, distillate
fuel oil, 347,O00, and others 1,483,000, a total of 7,505,000
barrels.
   California imports were: crude oil 252,000 barrels, and products
82,000, a total of 334,000 barrels, for a grand total of 7,839,000.
